    <p>{`The Vector `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`syslog`}</inlineCode>{` source
ingests data through the `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5424"
      }}>{`Syslog protocol`}</a>{` and outputs
`}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "/docs/about/data-model/log/"
      }}><inlineCode parentName="a">{`log`}</inlineCode></a>{` events.`}</p>
    {
      /*
          THIS FILE IS AUTOGENERATED!
           To make changes please edit the template located at:
           website/docs/reference/sources/syslog.md.erb
      */
    }
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "requirements"
    }}>{`Requirements`}</h2>
    <Alert icon={false} type="danger" className="list--icons list--icons--warnings" mdxType="Alert">
      <ul>
        <li parentName="ul">{`This component exposes a configured port. You must ensure your network allows access to this port.`}</li>
      </ul>
    </Alert>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "configuration"
    }}>{`Configuration`}</h2>
    <Tabs block={true} defaultValue="common" values={[{
      "label": "Common",
      "value": "common"
    }, {
      "label": "Advanced",
      "value": "advanced"
    }]} mdxType="Tabs">
      <TabItem value="common" mdxType="TabItem">
        <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
            "className": "language-toml",
            "metastring": "title=\"vector.toml\"",
            "title": "\"vector.toml\""
          }}>{`[sources.my_source_id]
  type = "syslog" # required
  address = "0.0.0.0:514" # required, required when mode = "tcp" or mode = "udp"
  mode = "tcp" # required
  path = "/path/to/socket" # required, required when mode = "unix"
`}</code></pre>
      </TabItem>
      <TabItem value="advanced" mdxType="TabItem">
        <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
            "className": "language-toml",
            "metastring": "title=\"vector.toml\"",
            "title": "\"vector.toml\""
          }}>{`[sources.my_source_id]
  # General
  type = "syslog" # required
  address = "0.0.0.0:514" # required, required when mode = "tcp" or mode = "udp"
  max_length = 102400 # optional, default, bytes
  mode = "tcp" # required
  path = "/path/to/socket" # required, required when mode = "unix"

  # Context
  host_key = "host" # optional, default

  # TLS
  tls.ca_file = "/path/to/certificate_authority.crt" # optional, no default
  tls.crt_file = "/path/to/host_certificate.crt" # optional, no default
  tls.enabled = false # optional, default
  tls.key_file = "/path/to/host_certificate.key" # optional, no default
  tls.key_pass = "\${KEY_PASS_ENV_VAR}" # optional, no default
  tls.verify_certificate = false # optional, default
`}</code></pre>
      </TabItem>
    </Tabs>
    <Fields filters={true} mdxType="Fields">
      <Field common={true} defaultValue={null} enumValues={null} examples={["0.0.0.0:514", "systemd", "systemd#2"]} groups={[]} name={"address"} path={null} relevantWhen={{
        "mode": ["tcp", "udp"]
      }} required={true} templateable={false} type={"string"} unit={null} warnings={[]} mdxType="Field">
        <h3 {...{
          "id": "address"
        }}>{`address`}</h3>
        <p>{`The TCP or UDP address to listen for connections on, or "systemd#N" to use the
Nth socket passed by systemd socket activation.`}</p>
      </Field>
      <Field common={false} defaultValue={"host"} enumValues={null} examples={["host"]} groups={[]} name={"host_key"} path={null} relevantWhen={null} required={false} templateable={false} type={"string"} unit={null} warnings={[]} mdxType="Field">
        <h3 {...{
          "id": "host_key"
        }}>{`host_key`}</h3>
        <p>{`The key name added to each event representing the current host. This can also
be globally set via the `}<a parentName="p" {...{
            "href": "/docs/reference/global-options/#host_key"
          }}>{`global [`}<inlineCode parentName="a">{`host_key`}</inlineCode>{`](#host_key)
option`}</a>{`.
See `}<a parentName="p" {...{
            "href": "#context"
          }}>{`Context`}</a>{` for more info.`}</p>
      </Field>
      <Field common={false} defaultValue={102400} enumValues={null} examples={[102400]} groups={[]} name={"max_length"} path={null} relevantWhen={null} required={false} templateable={false} type={"uint"} unit={"bytes"} warnings={[]} mdxType="Field">
        <h3 {...{
          "id": "max_length"
        }}>{`max_length`}</h3>
        <p>{`The maximum bytes size of incoming messages before they are discarded.`}</p>
      </Field>
      <Field common={true} defaultValue={null} enumValues={{
        "tcp": "Read incoming Syslog data over the TCP protocol.",
        "udp": "Read incoming Syslog data over the UDP protocol.",
        "unix": "Read uncoming Syslog data through a Unix socker."
      }} examples={["tcp", "udp", "unix"]} groups={[]} name={"mode"} path={null} relevantWhen={null} required={true} templateable={false} type={"string"} unit={null} warnings={[]} mdxType="Field">
        <h3 {...{
          "id": "mode"
        }}>{`mode`}</h3>
        <p>{`The input mode.`}</p>
      </Field>
      <Field common={true} defaultValue={null} enumValues={null} examples={["/path/to/socket"]} groups={[]} name={"path"} path={null} relevantWhen={{
        "mode": "unix"
      }} required={true} templateable={false} type={"string"} unit={null} warnings={[]} mdxType="Field">
        <h3 {...{
          "id": "path"
        }}>{`path`}</h3>
        <p>{`The unix socket path. `}<em parentName="p">{`This should be absolute path.`}</em></p>
      </Field>
      <Field common={false} defaultValue={null} enumValues={null} examples={[]} groups={[]} name={"tls"} path={null} relevantWhen={null} required={false} templateable={false} type={"table"} unit={null} warnings={[]} mdxType="Field">
        <h3 {...{
          "id": "tls"
        }}>{`tls`}</h3>
        <p>{`Configures the TLS options for connections from this source.`}</p>
        <Fields filters={false} mdxType="Fields">
          <Field common={false} defaultValue={null} enumValues={null} examples={["/path/to/certificate_authority.crt"]} groups={[]} name={"ca_file"} path={"tls"} relevantWhen={null} required={false} templateable={false} type={"string"} unit={null} warnings={[]} mdxType="Field">
            <h4 {...{
              "id": "ca_file"
            }}>{`ca_file`}</h4>
            <p>{`Absolute path to an additional CA certificate file, in DER or PEM format
(X.509), or an inline CA certificate in PEM format.`}</p>
          </Field>
          <Field common={true} defaultValue={null} enumValues={null} examples={["/path/to/host_certificate.crt"]} groups={[]} name={"crt_file"} path={"tls"} relevantWhen={null} required={false} templateable={false} type={"string"} unit={null} warnings={[]} mdxType="Field">
            <h4 {...{
              "id": "crt_file"
            }}>{`crt_file`}</h4>
            <p>{`Absolute path to a certificate file used to identify this server, in DER or PEM
format (X.509) or PKCS#12, or an inline certificate in PEM format. If this is
set and is not a PKCS#12 archive, `}<a parentName="p" {...{
                "href": "#key_file"
              }}><inlineCode parentName="a">{`key_file`}</inlineCode></a>{` must also be set. This is required
if `}<a parentName="p" {...{
                "href": "#enabled"
              }}><inlineCode parentName="a">{`enabled`}</inlineCode></a>{` is set to `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`true`}</inlineCode>{`.`}</p>
          </Field>
          <Field common={true} defaultValue={false} enumValues={null} examples={[false, true]} groups={[]} name={"enabled"} path={"tls"} relevantWhen={null} required={false} templateable={false} type={"bool"} unit={null} warnings={[]} mdxType="Field">
            <h4 {...{
              "id": "enabled"
            }}>{`enabled`}</h4>
            <p>{`Require TLS for incoming connections. If this is set, an identity certificate
is also required.`}</p>
          </Field>
          <Field common={true} defaultValue={null} enumValues={null} examples={["/path/to/host_certificate.key"]} groups={[]} name={"key_file"} path={"tls"} relevantWhen={null} required={false} templateable={false} type={"string"} unit={null} warnings={[]} mdxType="Field">
            <h4 {...{
              "id": "key_file"
            }}>{`key_file`}</h4>
            <p>{`Absolute path to a private key file used to identify this server, in DER or PEM
format (PKCS#8), or an inline private key in PEM format.`}</p>
          </Field>
          <Field common={true} defaultValue={null} enumValues={null} examples={["${KEY_PASS_ENV_VAR}", "PassWord1"]} groups={[]} name={"key_pass"} path={"tls"} relevantWhen={null} required={false} templateable={false} type={"string"} unit={null} warnings={[]} mdxType="Field">
            <h4 {...{
              "id": "key_pass"
            }}>{`key_pass`}</h4>
            <p>{`Pass phrase used to unlock the encrypted key file. This has no effect unless
`}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`key_file`}</inlineCode>{` is set.`}</p>
          </Field>
          <Field common={false} defaultValue={false} enumValues={null} examples={[false, true]} groups={[]} name={"verify_certificate"} path={"tls"} relevantWhen={null} required={false} templateable={false} type={"bool"} unit={null} warnings={[{
            "visibility_level": "option",
            "text": "Setting this to `false` will cause OpenSSL to not request a certificate from the client",
            "option_name": "verify_certificate"
          }]} mdxType="Field">
            <h4 {...{
              "id": "verify_certificate"
            }}>{`verify_certificate`}</h4>
            <p>{`If `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`true`}</inlineCode>{`, Vector will require a TLS certificate from the connecting host and
terminate the connection if it is not valid. If `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`false`}</inlineCode>{` (the default), Vector
will not request a certificate from the client.`}</p>
          </Field>
        </Fields>
      </Field>
    </Fields>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "fields"
    }}>{`Fields`}</h2>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-javascript",
        "metastring": "title=\"example log event\"",
        "title": "\"example",
        "log": true,
        "event\"": true
      }}>{`{
  // ...
  "appname": "app-name",
  "facility": "1",
  "host": "my.host.com",
  "hostname": "my.host.com",
  "message": "<13>Feb 13 20:07:26 74794bfb6795 root[8539]: i am foobar",
  "msgid": "ID47",
  "procid": "8710",
  "severity": "notice",
  "source_ip": "127.0.0.1",
  "timestamp": "2019-11-01T21:15:47+00:00",
  "version": 1,
  "custom_field1": "custom value 1"
  // ...
}
`}</code></pre>
    <Fields filters={true} mdxType="Fields">
      <Field common={false} defaultValue={null} enumValues={null} examples={["app-name"]} groups={[]} name={"appname"} path={null} relevantWhen={null} required={false} templateable={false} type={"string"} unit={null} warnings={[]} mdxType="Field">
        <h3 {...{
          "id": "appname"
        }}>{`appname`}</h3>
        <p>{`The appname extracted from the Syslog formatted line. If a appname is not
found, then the key will not be added.`}</p>
      </Field>
      <Field common={false} defaultValue={null} enumValues={null} examples={["1"]} groups={[]} name={"facility"} path={null} relevantWhen={null} required={false} templateable={false} type={"string"} unit={null} warnings={[]} mdxType="Field">
        <h3 {...{
          "id": "facility"
        }}>{`facility`}</h3>
        <p>{`The facility extracted from the Syslog line. If a facility is not found, then
the key will not be added.`}</p>
      </Field>
      <Field common={true} defaultValue={null} enumValues={null} examples={["my.host.com"]} groups={[]} name={"host"} path={null} relevantWhen={null} required={true} templateable={false} type={"string"} unit={null} warnings={[]} mdxType="Field">
        <h3 {...{
          "id": "host"
        }}>{`host`}</h3>
        <p>{`The hostname extracted from the Syslog line. If a hostname is not found, then
Vector will use the upstream hostname. In the case where `}<a parentName="p" {...{
            "href": "#mode"
          }}><inlineCode parentName="a">{`mode`}</inlineCode></a>{` = `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`"unix"`}</inlineCode>{` the
socket path will be used. This key can be renamed via the `}<a parentName="p" {...{
            "href": "#host_key"
          }}><inlineCode parentName="a">{`host_key`}</inlineCode></a>{` option.`}</p>
      </Field>
      <Field common={true} defaultValue={null} enumValues={null} examples={["my.host.com"]} groups={[]} name={"hostname"} path={null} relevantWhen={null} required={true} templateable={false} type={"string"} unit={null} warnings={[]} mdxType="Field">
        <h3 {...{
          "id": "hostname"
        }}>{`hostname`}</h3>
        <p>{`The hostname extracted from the Syslog line. (`}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`host`}</inlineCode>{` is also this value if it
exists in the log.)`}</p>
      </Field>
      <Field common={true} defaultValue={null} enumValues={null} examples={["<13>Feb 13 20:07:26 74794bfb6795 root[8539]: i am foobar"]} groups={[]} name={"message"} path={null} relevantWhen={null} required={true} templateable={false} type={"string"} unit={null} warnings={[]} mdxType="Field">
        <h3 {...{
          "id": "message"
        }}>{`message`}</h3>
        <p>{`The raw message, unaltered.
See `}<a parentName="p" {...{
            "href": "#parsing"
          }}>{`Parsing`}</a>{` for more info.`}</p>
      </Field>
      <Field common={false} defaultValue={null} enumValues={null} examples={["ID47"]} groups={[]} name={"msgid"} path={null} relevantWhen={null} required={false} templateable={false} type={"string"} unit={null} warnings={[]} mdxType="Field">
        <h3 {...{
          "id": "msgid"
        }}>{`msgid`}</h3>
        <p>{`The msgid extracted from the Syslog line. If a msgid is not found, then the key
will not be added.`}</p>
      </Field>
      <Field common={false} defaultValue={null} enumValues={null} examples={["8710"]} groups={[]} name={"procid"} path={null} relevantWhen={null} required={false} templateable={false} type={"string"} unit={null} warnings={[]} mdxType="Field">
        <h3 {...{
          "id": "procid"
        }}>{`procid`}</h3>
        <p>{`The procid extracted from the Syslog line. If a procid is not found, then the
key will not be added.`}</p>
      </Field>
      <Field common={false} defaultValue={null} enumValues={null} examples={["notice"]} groups={[]} name={"severity"} path={null} relevantWhen={null} required={false} templateable={false} type={"string"} unit={null} warnings={[]} mdxType="Field">
        <h3 {...{
          "id": "severity"
        }}>{`severity`}</h3>
        <p>{`The severity extracted from the Syslog line. If a severity is not found, then
the key will not be added.`}</p>
      </Field>
      <Field common={true} defaultValue={null} enumValues={null} examples={["127.0.0.1"]} groups={[]} name={"source_ip"} path={null} relevantWhen={null} required={true} templateable={false} type={"string"} unit={null} warnings={[]} mdxType="Field">
        <h3 {...{
          "id": "source_ip"
        }}>{`source_ip`}</h3>
        <p>{`The upstream hostname. In the case where `}<a parentName="p" {...{
            "href": "#mode"
          }}><inlineCode parentName="a">{`mode`}</inlineCode></a>{` = `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`"unix"`}</inlineCode>{` the socket path will
be used. (`}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`host`}</inlineCode>{` is also this value if `}<a parentName="p" {...{
            "href": "#hostname"
          }}><inlineCode parentName="a">{`hostname`}</inlineCode></a>{` does not exist in the log.)`}</p>
      </Field>
      <Field common={true} defaultValue={null} enumValues={null} examples={["2019-11-01T21:15:47+00:00"]} groups={[]} name={"timestamp"} path={null} relevantWhen={null} required={true} templateable={false} type={"timestamp"} unit={null} warnings={[]} mdxType="Field">
        <h3 {...{
          "id": "timestamp"
        }}>{`timestamp`}</h3>
        <p>{`The timestamp extracted from the incoming line. If a timestamp is not found,
then Vector will use the current time.`}</p>
      </Field>
      <Field common={false} defaultValue={null} enumValues={null} examples={[1]} groups={[]} name={"version"} path={null} relevantWhen={null} required={false} templateable={false} type={"int"} unit={null} warnings={[]} mdxType="Field">
        <h3 {...{
          "id": "version"
        }}>{`version`}</h3>
        <p>{`The version extracted from the Syslog line. If a version is not found, then the
key will not be added.`}</p>
      </Field>
      <Field common={false} defaultValue={null} enumValues={null} examples={[{
        "custom_field1": "custom value 1"
      }]} groups={[]} name={"`[field-name]`"} path={null} relevantWhen={null} required={false} templateable={false} type={"*"} unit={null} warnings={[]} mdxType="Field">
        <h3 {...{
          "id": "field-name"
        }}><inlineCode parentName="h3">{`[field-name]`}</inlineCode></h3>
        <p>{`In addition to the defined fields, any Syslog 5424 structured fields are parsed
and inserted as root level fields.`}</p>
      </Field>
    </Fields>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "examples"
    }}>{`Examples`}</h2>
    <p>{`Given the following `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5424"
      }}>{`Syslog 5424`}</a>{` log line:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-text"
      }}>{`<13>1 2020-03-13T20:45:38.119Z dynamicwireless.name non 2426 ID931 [exampleSDID@32473 iut="3" eventSource= "Application" eventID="1011"] Try to override the THX port, maybe it will reboot the neural interface!
`}</code></pre>
    <p>{`A `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`log`}</inlineCode>{` event will be produced with the following structure:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-javascript"
      }}>{`{
  "severity": "notice",
  "facility": "user",
  "timestamp": "2020-03-13T20:45:38.119Z",
  "host": "dynamicwireless.name", // controlled via the [\`host_key\`](#host_key) option,
  "source_ip": "127.0.0.1",
  "hostname": "dynamicwireless.name"
  "appname": "non",
  "procid": "2426",
  "msgid": "ID931",
  "iut": "3",
  "eventSource": "Application",
  "eventID": "1011",
  "message": "Try to override the THX port, maybe it will reboot the neural interface!"
}
`}</code></pre>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "how-it-works"
    }}>{`How It Works`}</h2>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "context"
    }}>{`Context`}</h3>
    <p>{`By default, the `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`syslog`}</inlineCode>{` source will add context
keys to your events via the `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "#host_key"
      }}><inlineCode parentName="a">{`host_key`}</inlineCode></a>{`
options.`}</p>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "environment-variables"
    }}>{`Environment Variables`}</h3>
    <p>{`Environment variables are supported through all of Vector's configuration.
Simply add `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`\${MY_ENV_VAR}`}</inlineCode>{` in your Vector configuration file and the variable
will be replaced before being evaluated.`}</p>
    <p>{`You can learn more in the
`}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "/docs/setup/configuration/#environment-variables"
      }}>{`Environment Variables`}</a>{` section.`}</p>
